President Obama expresses his support for Senator Menendez's bill to fix the broken immigration system in the United States. He commends the bill for including important building blocks from a bipartisan framework presented earlier in the year. The President believes that Senator Menendez and other members of Congress have shown critical leadership on this issue and emphasizes the need to move the debate forward. He urges elected officials from both parties to work together to address the challenges facing the nation and highlights the importance of comprehensive immigration reform for the economy and security. President Obama expresses his willingness to collaborate with members of both parties to accomplish this goal.